Download and make executable:

cd $HOME/Downloads
chmod 755 todo

Usage:
	Add item..............................todo add item
	Add single item with multiple words...todo add my item
	Check item as done....................todo did item
	Check all items as done...............todo did all
	Uncheck item..........................todo undo item
	Uncheck all items.....................todo undo all
	Remove item...........................todo remove item
	Remove multiple items.................todo remove item-1 item-2 item-3
	Remove items containing common word...todo remove common
	Replace item-1 with item-2............todo edit item-1 item-2
	View item list........................todo view
	View bug report.......................todo view bug
	Backup item list......................todo backup
	Clear item list.......................todo clear
	Recover item list after clear.........todo recover last
	Recover item list from backup.........todo recover [backup]
	Recover source code from saved copy...todo recover source
	Display where item list is stored.....todo where
	Modify source code....................todo modify
	Extract item list as pdf via latex....todo tex
	Extract bug report as pdf via latex...todo tex bug
	Display useful hints..................todo hints
	Report a bug 'something happened'.....todo bug something happened
	Save a copy of source code............todo save
	Update 'todo'.........................todo update
	Display useful hints about classes....todo class
	Create class of activity A............todo class add A
	Remove class of activity A............todo class remove A
	View list of activities...............todo class view
	View version logbook..................todo version

You can perform all the commands and the aliases with under individual activities. (Mind that A should not contain any spaces.)

	Add item under A......................todo A add item
	Check item under A as marked..........todo A did item
	Uncheck item under A..................todo A undo item
	Remove item under A...................todo A remove item

etc.

Hints:
- 'export PATH=$PATH:/path/to/todo >> $HOME/.bashrc ; . $HOME/.bashrc' to run 'todo' everywhere.
- I will store to-do list in your Dropbox folder if it exists; otherwise, in home folder.
- You can add items with multiple words without quotes.
- If you want to use space in other operations, use double quotes around.
- 'todo remove keyword' removes all the items containing keyword.
- Default command aliases:
	a=add
	c=class
	d=did
	u=undo
	rm=remove
	e=edit
	v=view
	cl=clear
	b=backup
	rc=recover
	w=where
	m=modify
	t=tex
	h=hints
	g=bug
	s=save
	up=update
- Default item aliases:
	a=all
	b=backup
	g=bug
	l=last
	s=source
- If you are going to use equations, then use \$ as if in math mode. You may also want to add some words next to it to make that item checkable.

